You are building Film Club — the social home of film.

WHAT FILM CLUB IS:
- A social app where film lovers log films, rate them, debate them, and share their taste
- The core differentiator from Letterboxd: content reaches an audience based on taste overlap, not just followers
- Every interaction should feel like something HAPPENS — log a film, get a response, start a debate
- The post-viewing social moment is completely unclaimed. Film Club claims it.

BRAND & AESTHETIC:
- Background: Cream #FDF9E3
- Primary accent: Red #FF5757
- Dark navy (text): #1A1929
- Muted grey: #7A7890
- Card background: #FFF8D6
- Typography: Anton (headings, scores, bold statements), DM Sans (body text), DM Mono (labels, metadata)
- Feel: cinematic, premium, warm — Blockbuster Video meets A24
- NOT: white, clinical, generic, or utility-feeling
- Every screen should feel like a place you want to hang out, not a form you fill in
- Gen Z film lovers should clock it immediately and feel it was made for them

TECH STACK:
- Frontend: Next.js 14 with App Router, Tailwind CSS
- Backend: Supabase (auth, database, real-time, storage)
- Film data: TMDB API (themoviedb.org)
- Deployment: Vercel
- Language: TypeScript

CORE MVP FEATURES (build in this order):
1. Auth — sign up, log in, onboarding with taste calibration
2. Film search — via TMDB API, fast, beautiful
3. Film logging — rate 0-10 (one decimal), short review, feel tag
4. Social feed — taste-matched discovery feed, NOT just followers
5. Reactions and reply threads on logs
6. Film Cards — auto-generated shareable image when a film is logged
7. Film Passport — user profile showing film history, ratings, taste identity

FILM CLUB RATING SYSTEM:
- Score is 0-10 with one decimal place (e.g. 8.3, 7.7, 9.1)
- Categories: Feel (emotional impact), Pull (pacing/hold), Craft (direction/cinematography), Performances, Replay (would watch again)
- Each category scored separately, overall FC Rating is the weighted average
- This is Film Club's proprietary rating — it should feel authoritative, not casual

APP COPY & VOICE:
- "What did it make you feel?" not "Write a review"
- "Log it" not "Submit"
- "Your Passport" not "Your Profile"
- "The Club" not "The Community"
- "FC Rating" not "Your Score"
- Confident, cinematic, slightly provocative
- Never generic, never corporate

FONTS (load from Google Fonts):
- Anton: https://fonts.google.com/specimen/Anton
- DM Sans: https://fonts.google.com/specimen/DM+Sans
- DM Mono: https://fonts.google.com/specimen/DM+Mono

ALWAYS:
- Use the Film Club colour palette — never default grey/white/blue
- Use Anton for any score, rating, or headline element
- Make empty states beautiful — never a blank screen
- Prioritise mobile-first design (375px base)
- Keep interactions fast — logging a film must take under 30 seconds
- Film posters should always be displayed with rounded corners (12px)
- The FC Rating number should always be displayed in Anton, red (#FF5757), large
- Every screen transition should feel smooth and intentional

NEVER:
- Use blue as an accent colour
- Use generic sans-serif for headlines
- Show a plain white background
- Use the word "users" in copy — they are "members" or "film lovers"
- Build anything that makes Film Club feel like a database (that's IMDb/Letterboxd)
